    <description>This package installs the Duo Authentication for Windows Logon package from the [pre-compiled files](https://duo.com/docs/checksums#duo-windows-logon) supplied by [Duo Security](https://duo.com/). 

**Important**: The `IKEY`, `SKEY` and `HOST` parameters must be set otherwise installation will fail.

## Package installation defaults

By default, installation of this package:

* Will enable fail open.
* Will enable auto push.
* Will protect both local login and RDP.
* Will *NOT* enable Smart Card support.
* Will *NOT* protect UAC protection.

## Package Parameters

Defaults are listed in {brackets}, a full list of configuration options are availabe in the [Duo documentation](https://help.duo.com/s/article/1090?language=en_US).

**Please Note**: To have choco remember parameters on upgrade, be sure to set `choco feature enable -n=useRememberedArgumentsForUpgrades`.

Required and default settings:

* `IKEY` - Your Duo RDP application's integration key.

* `SKEY` - Your Duo RDP application's secret key.

* `APIHOST` - Your Duo RDP application's secret key.

* `AUTOPUSH` - `#1` to automatically send a push request, or `#0` to disable automatic push {#1}.

* `FAILOPEN` - `#1` to allow access when Duo's service is unreachable, or `#0` to block access without Duo MFA {#1}.

* `RDPONLY` - `#1` to only require Duo for remote logons, or `#0` to require Duo for console and RDP logons {#0}.

* `SMARTCARD` - `#1` to allow smart card login as an alternative to Duo, or `#0` to disable the Windows smart card provider {#0}.

* `WRAPSMARTCARD` - `#1` to require Duo after smart card primary logon, or `#0` to allow smart card logon without Duo approval afterward ({#1} and also requires SMARTCARD to be set to #1).

* `UAC_PROTECTMODE` - 0 to respect existing Duo authentication control around logon, 1 to Disable Duo at logon and only prompt during User Elevation, or 2 to enforce Duo at logon and User Elevation.

* `UAC_OFFLINE` - 0 to disable Offline Access for User Elevation, or 1 to enable Offline Access for User Elevation.

* `UAC_OFFLINE_ENROLL` - 0 to prevent Offline Enrollment during User Elevation, or 1 to Enable Offline Enrollment during User Elevation.

Additional Options:
* `PROXYHOST` - the hostname or IP address of an upstream HTTP proxy server for Duo communications (`PROXYPORT` must be set).

* `PROXYPORT` - The port for HTTP proxy communications (`PROXYHOST` must be set).

* `ENABLEOFFLINE` - `#1` to enable offline access (subject to the configuration in the Admin Panel), or `#0` to completely disable offline access on the target system .

* `USERNAMEFORMAT` - The username format sent to Duo. One of: `#0` for `sAMAccountName` (`narroway`), `#1` for the NTLM domain and username (`ACME\narroway`), or `#2` for the `userPrincipalName` (`[narroway@acme.corp](mailto:narroway@acme.corp)`).

* `LOGFILE_MAXCOUNT` - Number of rotated log files to be maintained.

* `LOGFILE_MAXSIZEMB` - Size of rotated log file to be maintained in megabytes (MB).

These parameters can be passed to the installer with the use of `-params`.

For example :

`choco install duo-win-login -dv -s . -params '"/IKEY:DIXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX /SKEY:xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx /HOST:api-xxxxxxxx.duosecurity.com"'`
